# Creating the term dictionary of our courpus
dictionary_n_title = corpora.Dictionary(df["title_tokens"])
dictionary_n_text = corpora.Dictionary(df["text_tokens"])
In [8]:
# Converting list of documents (corpus) into Document Term Matrix using dictionary prepared above.
doc_term_matrix_n_title = [dictionary_n_title.doc2bow(doc) for doc in df["title_tokens"]]
doc_term_matrix_n_text = [dictionary_n_text.doc2bow(doc) for doc in df["text_tokens"]]

In [19]:
topics = ldamodel.print_topics(num_topics=19, num_words=15)
topic_data = []
for topic in topics:
    topic_words = topic[1].split('+')
    topic_words = [word.split('*')[1].strip().replace('"', '') for word in topic_words]
    topic_string = ", ".join(topic_words)
    topic_data.append((topic[0], topic_string))

df_topic_title = pd.DataFrame(topic_data, columns=['Topic', 'Words'])
print(df_topic_title)

topics = ldamodel_text.print_topics(num_topics=10, num_words=50)
topic_data = []
for topic in topics:
    topic_words = topic[1].split('+')
    topic_words = [word.split('*')[1].strip().replace('"', '') for word in topic_words]
    topic_string = ", ".join(topic_words)
    topic_data.append((topic[0], topic_string))

df_topic_text = pd.DataFrame(topic_data, columns=['Topic', 'Words'])
